The paper deals with the problem of estimating gradients of stochastic nodes in deep generative models, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper proposes a new method for gradient estimation that is applicable to various types of discrete random variables, which is relevant to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also includes experiments on topic modeling, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language), and synthetic data analyses, which could be relevant to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision).
